The European Union changes the rules for obtaining a visa
People must go to Visa Applicants Service Centers before their interview in the Consulate Section; the waiting time will be reduced.
As of 10 January 2011, the visa treatment procedure in the Embassy and consulates of the United States will change.
With the new procedure, the majority of applicants will have to present themselves at the Visa Applicants Service Centers (ASC, according to their English seals) before their interview in the Consular Section.
The ASC staff will take the biometric information of the applicant, which will be revised by the Consular Section before the interview.
The new procedure will provide certain benefits for aspirants, including the following:
The total cost of treating the visa will be lower, there will no longer be any need to make a payment to obtain an appointment, another payment for the treatment of the visa, and another for the mail service to register the document.
The aspirant will make a single payment that will cover the three services.
The current rate will remain the same: the equivalent of $140 for a tourist visa, $150 for visa with application (including visa for temporary workers) and $390 for traders and investors visa.
People who wish to renew their visa will not have to present themselves at an interview with the Consulate Representative, they will only present themselves to the closest ASC where they will present the documents and will take their fingerprints.
Due to the fact that biometric information will be collected in the ASC, applicants who wish a second appointment to be interviewed in the Consular Section will remain there less than before.
Similarly, visa applicants at the Consulates of Ciudad Juárez, Monterrey and Nuevo Laredo will no longer pay the extra service fee of $26.
For more information on the new visa application procedure, visit the following page http://mexico.usembassy.gov/boletines/sp101201_Visas-FAQs.html
