According to the proposed plan yesterday, if incandescent ampoules that still monopolize from 50 to 70% of the market were replaced by fluocompact ampoules or, better, by electroluminescent diodes (DEL or "LED"), the main humans would be 1.8 billion tonnes (Gt) of GES issued to the planet.
Lighting is responsible for 8% of global emissions.
This is the equivalent of 70% of the emissions of the planet car park.
Last year, in Copenhagen, major broadcasters, such as the United States, China, Europe and others, including Canada, engaged in voluntary reduction plans that would make total emissions of GES from 53 Gt to 49 Gt.
